      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DAVOLAS LEGACY NZ (3) is working towards a win having come from the back row to place in her last three outings, missing by just a head at Cranbourne last time. The good draw gives her the chance to break through. Hard to knock the form of LORD VERDE NZ (1) who made it three wins from his last four starts when leading to score at Stawell last time. This is stronger but he has the pace to take advantage of the ace draw. KYORETSU (4) should find this a little easier than recent attempts and came from this barrier when edged out narrowly three back at Bendigo. MORRIS BROWN (7) came from a similar draw to this and had to work but fought well for second at Ballarat last start. With better fortune he could go one better. SHAQ (2) will enjoy the low barrier having drawn wide and worked when placing at Shepparton last start and winning last month at Maryborough.",
